   <article class="post-23923 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-arts-humanities category-graduate-services category-literature" id="post-23923">
    <header class="entry-header">
     <h2 class="entry-title">
      <a href="https://update.lib.berkeley.edu/2019/03/04/new-books-added-to-graduate-services-in-march/" rel="bookmark">
       New Books Added to Graduate Services in March
      </a>
     </h2>
     <div class="entry-meta">
      <span class="posted-on">
       Posted on
       <a href="https://update.lib.berkeley.edu/2019/03/04/new-books-added-to-graduate-services-in-march/" rel="bookmark">
        <time class="entry-date published updated" datetime="2019-03-04T13:45:37-08:00">
         March 4, 2019
        </time>
       </a>
      </span>
      <span class="byline">
       by
       <span class="author vcard">
        <a class="url fn n" href="https://update.lib.berkeley.edu/author/spetersolibrary-berkeley-edu/">
         Scott Peterson
        </a>
       </span>
      </span>
     </div>
     <!-- .entry-meta -->
    </header>
    <!-- .entry-header -->
    <div class="entry-content">
     <p>
      <img alt="What is real?" src="https://coverart.oclc.org/ImageWebSvc/oclc/+-+1776682056_140.jpg?SearchOrder=+-+OT,OS,TN,AV,GO,FA"/>
     </p>
     <p>
      <a href="http://oskicat.berkeley.edu/record=b24796478~S1">
       What Is Real?
      </a>
      by Giorgio Agamben
     </p>
     <p>
      <img alt="The realness of things past ancient Greece and ontological history" src="https://coverart.oclc.org/ImageWebSvc/oclc/+-+1942210056_140.jpg?SearchOrder=+-+OT,OS,TN,AV,GO,FA"/>
     </p>
     <p>
      <a href="http://oskicat.berkeley.edu/record=b24818388~S1">
       The Realness Of Things Past: Ancient Greece And Ontological History
      </a>
      by Greg Anderson
     </p>
     <p>
      <img alt="HOW OLD IS THE HEBREW BIBLE? : a linguistic, textual, and historical study." src="https://coverart.oclc.org/ImageWebSvc/oclc/+-+1746434756_140.jpg?SearchOrder=+-+OT,OS,TN,AV,GO,FA"/>
     </p>
     <p>
      <a href="http://oskicat.berkeley.edu/record=b24796485~S1">
       How Old Is The Hebrew Bible?: A Linguistic, Textual, And Historical Study
      </a>
      by Ronald Hendel and Jan Joosten
     </p>
     <p>
      <img alt="Cathay : a critical edition" src="https://coverart.oclc.org/ImageWebSvc/oclc/+-+0364231256_140.jpg?SearchOrder=+-+OT,OS,TN,AV,GO,FA"/>
     </p>
     <p>
      <a href="http://oskicat.berkeley.edu/record=b24818363~S1">
       Cathay: A Critical Edition
      </a>
      by Ezra Pound edited by Timothy Billings
     </p>
    </div>
